# Conventional Commit Messages

Use the [Conventional Commits](https://www.conventionalcommits.org/) specification when generating commit messages.

## Format

```
<type>[optional scope]: <description>

[optional body]

[optional footer(s)]
```

## Types

| Type | Use when |
|------|----------|
| **feat** | New feature (MINOR in SemVer) |
| **fix** | Bug fix (PATCH in SemVer) |
| **build** | Build system or deps |
| **chore** | Maintenance tasks |
| **ci** | CI config changes |
| **docs** | Documentation only |
| **perf** | Performance improvement |
| **refactor** | Code change, no fix/feat |
| **style** | Formatting, whitespace |
| **test** | Adding or updating tests |

## Scope (optional)

Noun in parentheses: `feat(parser):`, `fix(auth):`

## Breaking Changes

- In footer: `BREAKING CHANGE: env vars now override config`
- Or in prefix: `feat(api)!: remove deprecated endpoint`

## Examples

```
feat(auth): add OAuth2 login flow
fix(parser): handle arrays with multiple spaces
docs: update API reference
refactor(backend): extract validation to utils

BREAKING CHANGE: drop support for Node 14
```

## Rules

- Description immediately after colon and space; imperative mood
- Body (if any) one blank line after description
- Footers one blank line after body; use `Token: value` or `Token #value`
- Types and scopes are case-insensitive; `BREAKING CHANGE` must be uppercase
